'''''Perry Mason: The Case of the Mandarin Murder''''' is an [[interactive fiction]] [[computer game]] with graphics. The game was published by [[Telarium]] (formerly known as Trillium), a subsidiary of [[Spinnaker Software]], in 1985.

==Description==
The game is based on the popular TV series ''[[Perry Mason (1957 TV series)|Perry Mason]]'' starring [[Raymond Burr]], who played the [[Perry Mason|fictional defense attorney of the same name]] created by [[Erle Stanley Gardner]]. The player must save client Laura Knapp from being convicted of the murder of her husband Victor.{{r|maher20140605}}

== Reception == 
''Antic Amiga'' in 1985 called ''Perry Mason'' "a major breakthrough in interactive fiction."<ref>Brad Kershaw: ''Perry Mason'', Antic Amiga Magazine, Vol. 5 Nr.1, 5/1985, p.81.</ref><ref name="maher20140605">{{cite web | url=http://www.filfre.net/2014/06/perry-mason-the-case-of-the-mandarin-murder/ | title=Perry Mason: The Case of the Mandarin Murder | work=The Digital Antiquarian | date=2014-06-05 | accessdate=11 July 2014 | author=Maher, Jimmy}}</ref>

